Class X509CA

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cesecore.internal.UpgradeableDataHashMap

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, IUpgradeableData
    public class X509CA
extends CA
implements Serializable
    X509CA is a implementation of a CA and holds data specific for Certificate and CRL generation according to the X509 standard.

      • createRequest

        public byte[] createRequest​(CryptoToken cryptoToken,
                            Collection<org.bouncycastle.asn1.ASN1Encodable> attributes,
                            String signAlg,
                            Certificate cacert,
                            int signatureKeyPurpose,
                            CertificateProfile certificateProfile,
                            AvailableCustomCertificateExtensionsConfiguration cceConfig)
                     throws CryptoTokenOfflineException,
                            CertificateExtensionException
        Description copied from class: CA
        Creates a certificate signature request (CSR), that can be sent to an external Root CA. Request format can vary depending on the type of CA. For X509 CAs PKCS#10 requests are created, for CVC CAs CVC requests are created.
        Specified by:
        createRequest in class CA
        Parameters:
        cryptoToken - Token
        attributes - PKCS10 attributes to be included in the request, a Collection of ASN1Encodable objects, ready to put in the request. Can be null.
        signAlg - the signature algorithm used by the CA
        cacert - the CAcertficate the request is targeted for, may be used or ignored by implementation depending on the request type created.
        signatureKeyPurpose - which CA token key pair should be used to create the request, normally SecConst.CAKEYPURPOSE_CERTSIGN but can also be SecConst.CAKEYPURPOSE_CERTSIGN_NEXT.
        certificateProfile - Certificate profile to use for CA-type specific purposes, such as CV Certificate Extensions.
        cceConfig - containing a list of available custom certificate extensions
        Returns:
        byte array with binary encoded request
        Throws:
        CryptoTokenOfflineException - if the crypto token is offline
        CertificateExtensionException - if there was a problem constructing a certificate extension.
        See Also:
        CA.createRequest(CryptoToken, Collection, String, Certificate, int, CertificateProfile, AvailableCustomCertificateExtensionsConfiguration)

      • generateCertificate

        public Certificate generateCertificate​(CryptoToken cryptoToken,
                                       EndEntityInformation subject,
                                       RequestMessage request,
                                       PublicKey publicKey,
                                       int keyusage,
                                       Date notBefore,
                                       Date notAfter,
                                       CertificateProfile certProfile,
                                       org.bouncycastle.asn1.x509.Extensions extensions,
                                       String sequence,
                                       CertificateGenerationParams certGenParams,
                                       AvailableCustomCertificateExtensionsConfiguration cceConfig)
                                throws CryptoTokenOfflineException,
                                       CAOfflineException,
                                       InvalidAlgorithmException,
                                       IllegalValidityException,
                                       IllegalNameException,
                                       org.bouncycastle.operator.OperatorCreationException,
                                       CertificateCreateException,
                                       CertificateExtensionException,
                                       SignatureException,
                                       IllegalKeyException
        Specified by:
        generateCertificate in class CA
        Parameters:
        request - provided request message containing optional information, and will be set with the signing key and provider. If the certificate profile allows subject DN override this value will be used instead of the value from subject.getDN. Its public key is going to be used if publicKey == null && subject.extendedInformation.certificateRequest == null. Can be null.
        publicKey - provided public key which will have precedence over public key from the provided RequestMessage but not over subject.extendedInformation.certificateRequest
        subject - end entity information. If it contains certificateRequest under extendedInformation, it will be used instead of the provided RequestMessage and publicKey
        cryptoToken - Token
        keyusage - BouncyCastle key usage X509KeyUsage, e.g. X509KeyUsage.digitalSignature | X509KeyUsage.keyEncipherment
        notBefore - Start date
        notAfter - End date
        certProfile - Profile
        extensions - an optional set of extensions to set in the created certificate, if the profile allows extension override, null if the profile default extensions should be used.
        sequence - an optional requested sequence number (serial number) for the certificate, may or may not be used by the CA. Currently used by CVC CAs for sequence field. Can be set to null.
        certGenParams - Extra parameters for certificate generation, e.g. for the CT extension. May contain references to session beans.
        cceConfig - containing a list of available custom certificate extensions
        Returns:
        the generated certificate
        Throws:
        CryptoTokenOfflineException - if the crypto token was unavailable
        CAOfflineException - if the CA wasn't active
        InvalidAlgorithmException - if the signing algorithm in the certificate profile (or the CA Token if not found) was invalid.
        IllegalValidityException - if validity was invalid
        IllegalNameException - if the name specified in the certificate request contains illegal characters
        org.bouncycastle.operator.OperatorCreationException - if CA's private key contained an unknown algorithm or provider
        CertificateCreateException - if an error occurred when trying to create a certificate.
        CertificateExtensionException - if any of the certificate extensions were invalid
        SignatureException - if the CA's certificate's and request's certificate's and signature algorithms differ
        IllegalKeyException - if the using public key is not allowed to be used by specified certProfile
